1
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:28,000
Gan'er, Gan'er.

2
00:01:28,159 --> 00:01:28,640
Mom.

3
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:30,239
You're so badly hurt.

4
00:01:30,359 --> 00:01:32,120
How could they be so vicious?

5
00:01:32,879 --> 00:01:33,599
Ning Chen, he...

6
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:35,359
He held an unauthorized trial,

7
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:36,680
and brutally tortured me.

8
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,760
He abused his power!

9
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:39,879
You must get justice for me, Mom.

10
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:40,920
Father, look at Gan'er.

11
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,519
Grandfather.

12
00:01:44,159 --> 00:01:44,799
Grandfather.

13
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,239
You must get justice for us.

14
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,359
Yes, Grandfather.

15
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,120
Grandfather.

16
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:49,879
Take him to be treated.

17
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,359
Go, quickly.

18
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,200
Mom, go on, go on.

19
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:52,959
Hurry, hurry.

20
00:01:55,319 --> 00:01:56,200
Silver Guard Ning.

21
00:01:57,079 --> 00:01:59,040
Quite the impressive display.

22
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,879
Even to your own kin,

23
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:04,400
you can be this ruthless.

24
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,920
You overstate it, Left Chancellor.

25
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,759
Half-brothers

26
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,919
hardly count as kin.

27
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:14,680
Besides,

28
00:02:15,919 --> 00:02:16,960
Paid by the Emperor,

29
00:02:17,319 --> 00:02:18,560
blessed by His grace,

30
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,319
I must set an example,

31
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:22,879
and not bend the law for personal gain.

32
00:02:23,919 --> 00:02:24,639
You, on the other hand—

33
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:27,080
cut off the tail to survive.

34
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:29,479
What a clever scheme.

35
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:32,400
I have no idea what you're talking about.

36
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:35,319
Left Chancellor,

37
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,840
Men act,

38
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:40,080
and Heaven is watching.

39
00:02:42,439 --> 00:02:43,439
We'll see about that.

40
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:51,439
Father,

41
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,639
how could he utter

42
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,840
such treasonous words?

43
00:02:55,879 --> 00:02:56,960
Whatever you have to say,

44
00:02:57,599 --> 00:02:58,879
save it for home.

45
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,280
Yes.

46
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,759
Commander Geng,

47
00:03:03,439 --> 00:03:06,039
I shall take my leave.

48
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,400
I won't see you out.

49
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:23,240
From now on,

50
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,759
the feud between Ning Chen and the Left Chancellor

51
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,879
will come out into the open.

52
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,080
You didn't say anything, did you?

53
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,280
Rest assured, Father.

54
00:03:40,439 --> 00:03:41,520
I didn't breathe a single word.

55
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,319
Remember,

56
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:44,960
as long as I'm here,

57
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,639
I'll keep you all safe.

58
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,560
But Father,

59
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,039
that bastard is getting more brazen.

60
00:03:52,639 --> 00:03:54,240
His Majesty sent him to quell bandits in Lingzhou.

61
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,520
What if he finds out about his mother—

62
00:04:01,319 --> 00:04:02,759
I have my own plans.

63
00:04:09,159 --> 00:04:09,960
Get over here.

64
00:04:12,599 --> 00:04:13,479
Father-in-law.

65
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,120
You can't even protect your own wife and son.

66
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,000
What a useless wretch.

67
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,639
Father-in-law, please calm your anger.

68
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,199
Ning Ziming,

69
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,160
you'd better remember this.

70
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,279
If you ever let my daughter

71
00:04:25,439 --> 00:04:26,600
and grandson suffer again,

72
00:04:27,399 --> 00:04:29,240
don't blame me for being merciless.

73
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,959
Rest assured, Father-in-law.

74
00:04:32,079 --> 00:04:33,879
This will never happen again.

75
00:04:41,959 --> 00:04:42,439
Madam,

76
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,319
Ning Chen will set out for war soon.

77
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:49,800
You have men at the front.

78
00:04:50,079 --> 00:04:51,560
By whatever means necessary,

79
00:04:51,879 --> 00:04:54,040
he must not return to the capital alive.

80
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,079
Rest assured.

81
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:08,839
Commander Geng.

82
00:05:09,279 --> 00:05:09,759
You wanted to see me?

83
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,959
For this campaign,

84
00:05:14,199 --> 00:05:14,800
Lao Pan,

85
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,040
Ziping,

86
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,079
and Qi Zheng

87
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:18,199
will go with you

88
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,240
to keep you safe.

89
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,079
Them?

90
00:05:21,839 --> 00:05:22,920
Maybe we should forget it.

91
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:24,319
They're great at investigations,

92
00:05:24,519 --> 00:05:26,399
but they're amateurs on the battlefield.

93
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,120
Weapons have no eyes on the battlefield.

94
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:29,720
You need a few men you can trust.

95
00:05:31,639 --> 00:05:33,040
This is also His Majesty's wish.

96
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,160
Fine, then.

97
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,759
You're all off duty for the next few days.

98
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,399
Go home and prepare.

99
00:05:42,319 --> 00:05:42,800
Yes, sir.

100
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:43,959
And one more thing.

101
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:51,160
The men of the Imperial Inspectorate

102
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,600
must come back alive.

103
00:05:59,399 --> 00:05:59,879
Understood.

104
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:03,800
Get the hell out.

105
00:06:07,759 --> 00:06:08,160
My lord.

106
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:08,680
My lord.

107
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,759
You're here.

108
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,480
Come find me next time.

109
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:12,720
Master Ning.

110
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,000
Ning Chen, let's have a chat.

111
00:06:20,879 --> 00:06:21,360
Please.

112
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:25,720
No wonder they say the Music Bureau

113
00:06:25,879 --> 00:06:27,600
is the biggest money-sink in the capital.

114
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:30,560
It's even more lavish than my Eastern Palace.

115
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,120
Comparing a brothel to the Eastern Palace?

116
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,759
You're really something.

117
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,240
Dear Ning, you're here.

118
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:39,480
Die'er.

119
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:43,199
This must be Miss Yudie.

120
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:46,199
I greet you, Master.

121
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,399
No need for formalities.

122
00:06:48,079 --> 00:06:48,959
Rumor has it

123
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,480
the Music Bureau has Twelve Chambers,

124
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,759
and the ladies of each chamber

125
00:06:51,959 --> 00:06:53,839
are all peerless beauties.

126
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,319
Meeting Miss Yudie today,

127
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,120
I see the rumors are true.

128
00:06:58,959 --> 00:07:01,120
I hear Miss Yudie's pipa playing

129
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:02,720
is unmatched in the capital.

130
00:07:03,319 --> 00:07:05,879
Might I have the honor?

131
00:07:06,079 --> 00:07:07,480
No, you may not.

132
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,600
Be glad you're getting wine.

133
00:07:09,959 --> 00:07:11,920
And you want my woman to play for you?

134
00:07:12,199 --> 00:07:12,319
You...

135
00:07:12,439 --> 00:07:15,199
Should I dance to liven things up too?

136
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,000
No, thank you.

137
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:19,839
Die'er.

138
00:07:20,199 --> 00:07:20,800
Could you please

139
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:22,600
prepare some fine wine and food for us?

140
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,319
Of course, Dear Ning.

141
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:40,319
Have a seat.

142
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,399
Ning Chen,

143
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,319
you're a lucky man with the ladies.

144
00:07:46,879 --> 00:07:48,600
The Twelve Chambers of the Music Bureau

145
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,519
have more than just Yudie and Nanzhi.

146
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,560
The other ladies

147
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,160
are all stunning beauties too.

148
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,519
Why don't I find one for you?

149
00:07:58,079 --> 00:07:58,600
Forget it.

150
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:01,959
Coming to the Music Bureau is already going too far.

151
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:07,839
What do you mean?

152
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,839
One hundred taels per cup.

153
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,000
No.

154
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,120
What kind of wine is this?

155
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:15,199
Wine of friendship.

156
00:08:15,639 --> 00:08:17,959
Friendship is priceless.

157
00:08:19,759 --> 00:08:20,600
Well said.

158
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:25,959
Stop counting.

159
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:27,879
A friend arrives from afar,

160
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,839
is that not a joy?

161
00:08:28,879 --> 00:08:29,439
Today,

162
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,399
I'll make sure you drink to your heart's content.

163
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:31,959
Come on.

164
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:33,159
Ning Chen.

165
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,360
The only one bold enough to snatch silver from me,

166
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,200
in all of Great Xuan,

167
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:39,519
is you.

168
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,840
I have to think

169
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,440
of how to punish you.

170
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,440
How about this?

171
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,919
I'll punish myself with three cups.

172
00:08:46,279 --> 00:08:46,759
Sound fair?

173
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,320
In your dreams.

174
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,639
Six hundred taels in total.

175
00:08:49,759 --> 00:08:50,600
Six cups of wine.

176
00:08:50,759 --> 00:08:51,519
Three each.

177
00:08:51,879 --> 00:08:52,720
No cheating.

178
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,200
So stingy.

179
00:08:55,919 --> 00:08:57,960
So stingy, and you call yourself the Crown Prince?

180
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:01,399
Greetings, Crown Prince.

181
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,480
This humble one didn't know it was Your Highness.

182
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,919
Please forgive me, Your Highness.

183
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,360
No need for formalities.

184
00:09:06,519 --> 00:09:06,919
Rise.

185
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:08,679
Don't be nervous.

186
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,200
He's a good guy.

187
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,080
But he's the Crown Prince!

188
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,879
The future Xuandi.

189
00:09:15,519 --> 00:09:17,600
Dear Ning is so close with him?

190
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,120
That's amazing.

191
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,360
Dear Ning.

192
00:09:22,639 --> 00:09:25,000
I hear the Northern Frontier is colder than the capital.

193
00:09:25,759 --> 00:09:26,440
I

194
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,240
had some thick robes made for you.

195
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:31,279
There's a scented sachet inside.

196
00:09:31,879 --> 00:09:33,279
I made it myself.

197
00:09:33,679 --> 00:09:34,879
I hope you like it, Dear Ning.

198
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:37,559
Of course I do.

199
00:09:39,799 --> 00:09:40,679
Don't worry about me.

200
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,360
I'm blessed with great fortune.

201
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,200
Wait for my triumphant return.

202
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:46,639
You take good care of yourself.

203
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,559
I'll be waiting for you.

204
00:09:50,279 --> 00:09:50,759
All right.

205
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,000
The battlefield is treacherous.

206
00:09:55,759 --> 00:09:57,480
Huai'an asked me to tell you,

207
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:00,080
to be extra careful.

208
00:10:03,679 --> 00:10:04,840
Who's Huai'an?

209
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,519
A ringleader. Not important.

210
00:10:07,879 --> 00:10:09,039
I've just had drinks with him a few times.

211
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:09,720
Come on.

212
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,759
Crown Prince.

213
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:11,480
Let's drink. Come on.

214
00:10:11,679 --> 00:10:12,320
These six cups,

215
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,960
today we won't stop till we're drunk.

216
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:14,759
No.

217
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,799
You can't drink from that.

218
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:17,279
You've got to use this.

219
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:17,879
No.

220
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:20,360
Since you've bought my Yudie's wine today,

221
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:22,679
we two won't stop till we're drunk.

222
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,120
Come on.

223
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:23,679
Cheers.

224
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:24,480
Drink up!

225
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,039
You little rascal.

226
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,159
With that armor on,

227
00:10:30,799 --> 00:10:32,960
you really look like I did back in my day.

228
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,799
Bold and resolute.

229
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:36,759
When you return,

230
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:39,639
I'll have a surprise for you.

231
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:40,879
All right.

232
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,600
Verbal Edict from His Majesty.

233
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,600
Wait, wait, wait.

234
00:10:48,559 --> 00:10:49,440
His Majesty said,

235
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:50,519
no need to kneel.

236
00:10:51,039 --> 00:10:52,519
He told you to stand and listen.

237
00:10:57,399 --> 00:10:58,039
His Majesty said,

238
00:10:58,559 --> 00:11:01,159
take good care of yourself on the road,

239
00:11:01,679 --> 00:11:03,279
and come back safe and sound.

240
00:11:04,559 --> 00:11:06,159
Get your ass back here alive to see Me.

241
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:10,679
This general will do as you command.

242
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:13,200
And one more thing.

243
00:11:22,919 --> 00:11:23,799
Thrifty at home, generous on the road.

244
00:11:24,519 --> 00:11:25,679
Take this money with you.

245
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,080
This is...

246
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,960
This is what I've saved up for ages.

247
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,559
Don't go wasting it.

248
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:35,799
You...

249
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,559
You must come back alive.

250
00:11:38,159 --> 00:11:39,720
Come back alive to see me.

251
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:41,799
Thank you, Uncle Quan.

252
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,159
Let's go.

253
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:53,480
Old General.

254
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,600
While I'm away from the capital,

255
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,919
I'd like to trouble you, Old General,

256
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,840
to look after Yudie and Xiao Mei for me.

257
00:12:00,759 --> 00:12:02,200
If anyone dares to cross them,

258
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:04,960
please make a note of it, Old General.

259
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:06,879
When I return,

260
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,679
I'll settle the score with each of them.

261
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:12,200
Don't you worry.

262
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:15,519
You'd better take care of yourself first.

263
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:19,720
I'm off.

264
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:50,320
Dear Ning.

265
00:12:51,159 --> 00:12:51,759
My Pan.

266
00:13:24,039 --> 00:13:24,919
The east wind blows,

267
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:26,799
the war drums sound,

268
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,679
the beauty grows tipsy,

269
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,120
longing for your return.

270
00:13:32,679 --> 00:13:33,639
News of victory soars,

271
00:13:35,159 --> 00:13:36,240
the hero comes home.

272
00:13:39,039 --> 00:13:42,120
May I be the bright moon walking by your side,

273
00:13:43,679 --> 00:13:47,519
May moonbeams light your way each night.
